SW:<br><br>
Thanks for the info.<br><br>
It takes twelve dollars and thirty seven cents to train a Warrant Officer candidate to fly.. but it costs the tax payer eight million dollars to teach him how to be an officer and a gentleman.  In my case, it was twenty four million (I was recycled three times.)<br><br>
When you look at the fuel these boys burn and figure the costs of providing equipment (on top of the change required to get them trained) seems prudent that Uncle Sam would pay them major bucks...at least as much as some martini swilling airline captain makes for flying 80 hours a month...with all the other bennies.<br><br>
Of course we could just train grunts.. you know... a couple of cases of coloring books and crayons... a few cases of electric shock dog collars a few cans of shineola (one can per DI), an old TV set and a couple video tapes of &quot;F Troop&quot; and you got the beginnings of a Marine Corps Infantry Company. <br><br>
